course_title: Women's Health Gender Related Nurse Practitioner II
class_notes: Online asynchronous and synchronous sessions. Face-to-face intensives dates: TBD
course_description: The focus of this course is on the delivery of obstetrical health care beginning with preconception through the post-partum period. Ethical and social considerations surrounding maternal morbidity and mortality will be addressed.
prerequisites: NRSG 581D or equivalent transfer credit as prerequisite.
